*Child abuse cases on the rise amidst lockdown*üö´
.
A PTI report stated that during March 20-31, the first week of the lockdown, the Childline India helpline ‘CHILDLINE 1098’ received over 92,000 SOS calls from across the country, asking for protection from abuse and violence. 
(Report- Hindustan Times)üóûÔ∏è
.
Being the dependent ones in the family, children regardless of their gender do suffer the "invisible" abuse.üõë
.
1. Start talking about the basics of sexual reproduction when children are around five-years.üìö
.
2. Teach them that some body parts are private.‚úã
.
3. Tell your child that body secrets are not okay.üëé
.
4. Teach your child to say an absolute NO.üôÖ‍‚ôÇÔ∏è
.
5. Tell your child that these rules apply even with people they know and even with another child.üë®‍üë©‍üëß‍üë¶

node.text:
When the intention is there, everything is possible

Traveling from D√ºsseldorf to Moscow during #covidtimes

DUS - AYT:

#Airport DUS is quite empty. Everything goes much faster as no/less people are there. I've got a feeling that only flights to Turkey go from international departures here. In D√ºDo +15 degrees centigrade.

‚úàÔ∏è‚û°Ô∏èAYT: no #socialdistancing at all. Very strict rules of wearing the #masks. In general, everything as usual (before Corona) apart from that everyone wear all these masks. Unbelievable that we almost breath into each others shoulder during 4 hours flight while continuosly hearing about keeping the distance. Absurd to my opinion.

AYT: Airport full of people. + 35 degrees centigrade. Thinking of staying there üòä 

Pass control, picking up the luggage, checking in again. Independent transfer. Taking a taxi to another terminal 2 to catch the Pobeda flight. 

AYT - VKO: Much softer and easier way of wearing the masks - one can feel the russian mood already there. The plane is full of people.

‚úàÔ∏è‚û°Ô∏èVKO: Pass control as usual. Additional stage for filling the form about Covid - that's it. Easy. Covid test still to be done within next 3 days.

And then... home sweet home and Papa picking me up‚ô•Ô∏è

‚ûï Got to know extremely interesting and nice people. Time passed really quick, although I was #traveling the whole day long.
